Comment: This is my traditional opening, the King's Pawn Game (B00).
I've rarely experienced this opener before, which is Alekhine's Defense (B02). I knew though that against someone this strong, this would be expected.

Normally, I'd protect my pawn, but with being against a master, and getting better at chess lately, I felt that the Alekhine's Defense Mokele Mbembe (Buecker) Variation (B02) was a good idea. Stalhandske told me that this was a good move.
Black continues the Alekhine's Defense (B02).
I continue the Alekhine's Defense (B02) by attacking the knight again.
The Alekhine's Defense Steiner Variation (B02) continues.
I respond with the Alekhine's Defense (B02) two pawns' (Lasker's) Attack. Again, black tells me this is a good move, which I am glad to hear, for I'm usually good with openings.
Black plays the Alekhine's Defense (B02) two pawns' attack Mikenas Variation.
I continue Alekhine.
Black continues Alekhine.

Alekhine's Defense is now over, along with the book openings. Quite impressive though that both sides, namely white, was able to stay with the book for 5 moves. Now the game continues without the book,
If I do not play cxb6, black will probably play b5 next and attack my Bishop...
...so I decide to attack and trade.
This would of continued Alekhine's Defense if played on move 6.
This would of continued Alekhine's Defense if played on move 6.

Wasn't completely expecting fair trade, but I'll except. Knights can be powerful pieces, but in this case it doesn't really matter for each side because it's a fair trade and neither Knight is a threat.
My Bishop gets attacked.
My Bishop gets attacked.
I play check, which may not be the best move, but not the worse.
I expected this move. I basically gave white a free move, and now I must protect my Bishop to.
I think black may be planning more trade, but could also be trying to control center.
I think black may be planning more trade, but could also be trying to control center.

I played the opening of this game quite well, but finally I made an inaccuracy, which wasn't a bad move, but computer analysis says that Nf3 would of been better, which yes it would of, for it would of got my knight out there.
